t%20rains%2C%20it's%20a%20wipeout.%20And%20so%20I%20was%20with%20the%20architects%20that%20were%20designing%2C%20it's%20going%20to%20be%20incredible%2C%26quot%3B%20Trump%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20they%20came%20in.%20They%20said%2C%20'Charlie%20Kirk%20is%20dead.'%20I%20didn't%20know%20what%20they%20meant.%20I%20said%2C%20'What%20do%20you%20mean%2C%20dead%3F%20Charlie%20Kirk%20was%20shot.'%20And%20they%20thought%20he%20was%20dead%20cuz%20it%20was%20so%20horrific%2C%20you%20know%2C%20and%20I%20said%2C%20'Dead%3F'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20show%20then%20cuts%20back%20to%20Kimmel.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EKimmel%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%26quot%3BAnd%20then%20we%20installed%20the%20most%20beautiful%20chandelier.%20Sconces%20you%20wouldn't%20believe.%20There's%20something%20wrong%20with%20them.%20There%20really%20is.%20I%20mean%2C%20who%20thinks%20like%20that%3F%20And%20why%20are%20we%20building%20a%20%24200%20million%20ballroom%20in%20the%20White%20House%3F%20Is%20it%20possible%20that%20he's%20doing%20it%20intentionally%2C%20so%20we%20could%20be%20mad%20about%20that%20instead%20of%20the%20Epstein%20list%3F%20By%20the%20time%20he's%20out%20of%20office%2C%20the%20White%20House%20will%20have%20slot%20machines%20in%20a%20water%20slide.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EKimmel%20then%20called%20out%20Trump%20for%20being%20in%20a%20%26quot%3Bmajor%20change-the-subject%20mode.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EKimmel%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%26quot%3BOn%20Friday%2C%20he%20stopped%20by%20the%20always-friendly%20morning%20crew%20at%20Fox.%20Whenever%20Trump%20goes%20on%20Fox%20and%20Friends%2C%20it's%20funny%20because%20the%20hosts%20are%20so%20eager%20for%20him%20to%20be%20reasonable.%20They%20spell%20it%20all%20out%20for%20him.%20They%20desperately%20want%20to%20avoid%20having%20to%20nod%20along%20with%20anything%20crazy%20or%20contradict%20him%2C%26quot%3B%20Kimmel%20said.%20%26quot%3BSo%2C%20they%20give%20him%20the%20question%20and