rtup%20building%20an%20AI%20search%20engine%20for%20doctors%2C%20first%20sued%20Doximity%20in%20June%2C%20claiming%20the%20%2413%20billion%20public%20healthcare%20company%20impersonated%20doctors%20to%20steal%20its%20trade%20secrets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20Doximity%20is%20accusing%20OpenEvidence%20of%20spreading%20inaccurate%20information%20about%20itself%20and%20Doximity%20to%20undermine%20Doximity's%20reputation%20and%20poach%20its%20employees%2C%20according%20to%20its%20complaint%20filed%20Wednesday%20in%20Massachusetts'%20federal%20district%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDoximity%20also%20moved%20to%20dismiss%20OpenEvidence's%20original%20complaint%20on%20Monday%2C%20calling%20the%20June%20lawsuit%20an%20attempt%20to%20%26quot%3Bstifle%20fair%20competition.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20disputes%20between%20the%20two%20companies%20began%20even%20earlier%20this%20year.%20In%20February%2C%20OpenEvidence%20filed%20a%20similar%20lawsuit%20against%20Canadian%20AI%20startup%20Pathway%20Medical%2C%20accusing%20the%20AI-powered%20clinical%20decision%20support%20company%20of%20making%20%26quot%3Bprompt%20injection%26quot%3B%20attacks%20to%20access%20the%20system%20prompts%20behind%20OpenEvidence's%20AI%20and%20use%20them%20to%20train%20Pathway's%20AI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPathway%20sought%20to%20dismiss%20that%20case%20in%20June.%20In%20August%2C%20Doximity%20acquired%20Pathway%20for%20%2463%20million.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOpenEvidence%20sued%20a%20third%20competitor%2C%20Vera%20Health%2C%20on%20similar%20claims%20of%20prompt%20injection%20attacks%20in%20June.%20Vera%20Health%20hasn't%20yet%20responded%20to%20the%20lawsuit%20in%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOpenEvidence's%20efforts%20may%20very%20well%20be%20a%20test%20bed%20for%20new%20legal%20precedents.%20The%20startup's%20legal%20battles%20with%20Doximity%2C%20Pathway%2C%20and%20Vera%20Health%20are%20among%20the%20first%20instances%20of%20a%20company%20suing%20a%20competitor%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsid